C=N
\sqrt{r(\theta)^2+r'(\theta)^2}=2r'(\theta). 
r'(\theta)^2=\frac{1}{3} r(\theta)^2 
\frac{\mathrm{d} r}{\mathrm{d} \theta}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} r, 
r(\theta)=C \mathrm{e}^{\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} \theta }.
r(\theta)=N \mathrm{e}^\frac{\theta}{\sqrt{3}}. 
